description: A compilation of Howard Cruse's gay-themed comic strips and comic book stories published between 1976 and 2008, with supplementary background material and a few unpublished extras. Some stories originally appeared in adults-only underground comix; for that reason this book carries a "for mature readers" warning.

After several years in prison Andy is finally out on parole, ready to build a new life for himself. But first he has to see Todd, Andy's old partner in crime and the reason he went away. For weeks Todd has been begging for them to meet, claiming that he has something important to tell him. Andy reluctantly agrees.

Joachim Bischoff, named after Saint Joachim, a Teutonic Knight and crusader but definitely no saint. A man of great violence who thought he had found his ordained role in life, purging central Europe of pagans, soon discovered that he had lost his God.

Roy Wallis is, for all appearances, a normal boy from a normal loving family. That is why his crime shocked his loved ones so. Sent to a central European young person's reform camp he thinks his future is tainted and the undercurrent of anger within the boy boils to the surface once more.

The Knights of Cademus are a century's old order. The elite warriors of the Book of Cademus, their belief in their cause, their brothers and their Lord drives them. How is such an order of human weapons forged?

A Prince of the Blood

A 15-year old kid in Anacostia, Washington, DC, is about to have his life turned upside down when his ancestors cause a magic talisman to be placed where it will save his life and he finds himself transformed into a creature of legend, the Lionman!

Volume 1 (IN COLOR!)

Do you hate inanimate objects? Do you love America? Do you like supporting strange shadowy organizations that claim to sell comic books?

Then you'll love Man Vs. Rock! Named Indie Comic Book of the year (Comic Bastards), this is the timeless tale of an insane geology professor hell bent on getting revenge on rocks. Yes, you read that correctly. I said rocks.

Eva's desire to prove herself as a future guardian for the monsters of the halfway house, is prematurely put to the test when her father is attacked. She must go rescue him from Shadow Falls, the monsters' world.

The Octopus is a comic about a young school girl who lives in an imaginary world of her own making. She loves scientific facts and learning about the ocean but sometimes bleeds reality with fantasy by making up her own facts. On a school field trip to the aquarium she meets an octopus who begins to take over her mind.

Atari Gashi, the most beautiful and famous teenage girl in all of Planet X is kidnapped by a mercenary gang of thugs for randsom. But when their getaway van is blown up by a chainsaw wielding masked avenger named Chainsaw, Atari finds herself along for the ride in a treasure hunting caper for a legendary magic sword called the Sword of Eternal Shadow.

The Earth has been divided into three dominions: the Vladok Alliance, Nakatami Corps and the New Union of Democratic States. The planet is dying because of pollution and the exploitation of natural resources. Yet there is hope. A newly discovered world still unspoiled and fertile known as "Hope." Armies from each dominion, desperate to claim the planet as their own, invade Hope. It is war! General Stadler, Supreme Commander of the armies of the Vladok Alliance, sends troops to Hope.

Troops that have been created in a laboratory and genetically perfected, for which the general has spent numerous years and the state's money to create. His soldiers are equipped with artificial memories, customized for the individual to motivate them in combat. They all believe they have a family waiting for them at home. A soldier's average lifespan is 300 years and they are immune to any form of aging.

Entry Wound

Monster Miami, 198X. Hank, a middle-aged Troll and former Chief of Police gets his little slice of heaven blown to pieces. Seeking answers, he teams up with Mike, an arson aficionado and small-time criminal. Together, they track down whosever brave enough to put a hit out on The Chief of @#$%-ing Police.

The first chapter of the series introduces us to the amazing world of Tenebra with its colorful and diversified inhabitants. As the free clans are threatened and enslaved by dark forces, it's up to a small group of insurgents around the mysterious off-worlder Uri and his adopted son Loan to take a stand against the demonic usurper Noctus. Will the strange girl in the cocoon, whom Loan recovers in a hidden cave, help them - or lead to their downfall?
name: Book 1: Seed of Hope

volume.name: Ria: The Lightclan Chronicles: Seed of Hope

description: Rock and Roll Biographies featuring Iron Maiden! One of the few bands Todd Loren and Revolutionary Comics never got to produce due to legal issues! See how Iron Maiden formed, and learn how their monstrous mascot 'Eddie' was created. Forty years of pure metal madness encompassed in 32 pages of comic book history-in-the-making! A must for every Iron Maiden fan!

Gamekocks from all over the world come to compete for honor, glory and legacy. This is the story of Jonny, a young and inexperienced fighter who wants to join the club and become the champ. He travels to the Big City to find McCluck, a veteran fighter who has lost his direction. After two fighters mysteriously go missing, Jonny and McCluck soon discover the horrible truth behind The Rooster Rumble Fight Club. It is an action-filled story with great characters that is about the fight to redeem a heart filled with empty promises. What do you fight for?
name: GN

description:
Adorable and super-talented Takase is the star secretary of his company! His reputation's been built on his amazing ability to make anyone he works with a success...but what will happen when he's assigned to the lazy son of the big boss? Can a prodigy improve the reputation of a handsome slacker? Secretary's Job works overtime to prove that good-looks and charisma go a long way in the workplace! It's lots of fun to tackle meetings with the company's best employee, but will a professional relationship cross the line once sweet, surprising feelings come to light?

Contents

  • Secretary's Job?
  • I'll Make You My Prisoner!
  • Falling In Love With You
  • Jealousy 1
  • Jealousy 2
name: Vol. 1

description: A QUARTET OF LEGENDARY STARFLEET CAPTAINS GET THEIR DUE IN THIS THRILLING AND REVEALING COLLECTION OF ONE-SHOTS! See how Captains Pike, Sulu, Harriman, and Jellico handle the responsibilities and challenges they face as Starfleet captains.
name: TPB

description: His friend James T. Kirk has been promoted to Admiral, the U.S.S. Enterprise is in space dock for a refit, so McCoy is on his own as a member of the Frontier Medics Program in this collection of lively tales written and illustrated by John Byrne. Share the adventure as Bones confronts a mysterious plague on a distant world, contends with his growing distaste for the transporter, fights a virus that just might be smarter than he is, and wrestles with a dilemma that cuts to the very heart of his Hippocratic Oath. Along the way pick up story threads from Byrne's other Star Trek series, Assignment: Earth and Crew
name: TPB

volume.name: Star Trek: Leonard McCoy: Frontier Doctor

description: The most dangerous experimental vessel in the galaxyâa prototype time shipâhas vanished and it appears that the man who stole it is none other than Starfleet Admiral Edward Jellico. Only Mackenzie Calhoun and the crew of Excalibur have a hope in finding him before the ship, intended purely for scientific exploration, is used to disrupt the space-time continuum!
name: TPB

description: William Ness has just become the underworld kingpin. Police Captain Jonathan Moretti now considers Ness the most dangerous man in Chicago, and asks for the case. Moretti reveals his great-uncle was Al Capone (Jonathan Capone Moretti) and he now wants justice for the city and to right his family's name.
name: GN

description: The Verge: Materia Nigra is a revenge story set in a dead memory. With art and narrative referring to the more psychedelic sci-fi pop culture can conceive.

The Wildlands opens with a small family of gorillas lead by Ambam living peacefully on a remote southern island in the Ankhari Isles. However, when a stranger washes up on their shores, Ambam will struggle to keep his family safe from those looking for this stranger, and the dangerous times that lay ahead.

The city of Antipolo has a Dying problem. Or rather, an UNDEAD problem! Three vampiric Aswang prowl the streets, causing a citywide panic as more and more children disappear. Can Bayani and Tala rescue Lil Drigo before he's just another pint-sized victim? For readers of all ages.
name: And the Dying City

description:
The Games

Dr. Wagner heads back to the city to get more Chem to keep Vivian alive.
name: The Games

description:
Part Two

A mysterious and dangerous gunslinger arrives in the outback town of Durham, just as tensions between the deadly Stewart family and other locals simmer to boiling point.
name: Part Two

description:
Warm Starts

End of Act 1. Reunions and introductions are brief as the OtherWorlders set up a hidden camp along the Cailfornia coast to take advantage of the nearby, benthic pool of Magyx. Abbadon bears down on the Conjuror Zero. The climactic end to Book 1 relaunches Kenneth and the OtherWorlders into new worlds of adventure.
name: Warm Starts

description: Eva continues her quest into the monster world of Shadow Falls to rescue her father. But she might fail to find him before she becomes one of the monsters.
What happened to Raceway? What plans are Vycia and Cataclysm hatching? Plus - see if Sonaru fits the "hero" mold defined by Vindic!
name: Out of Hand

description: The origin of Raceway - what happened to his wife? Plus: Stonefish gets her TLB!

When you work for Black Ops Social Services, there's never a slow day at the office. Maybe today's the day the clockwork receptionist's evil gears will kick in. Maybe the office supplies will vote to go on strike. Maybe a mad scientist will escape the facility and go on a high fashion funkadelic rampage.

But with a lot of hard work and a little bit of topless mud-wrestling, the staff of Project Skin Horse will get the job done.

Civil service style.
name: Volume Three

description:
Chapter 20

Still down after getting dumped by Melanie, Danny goes on a disaster date.
name: Chapter 20

description:
That time again, huh? Well, I guess this is where we tell you about the last issue of Soul Men... Last issue we saw Cliff, Rigby, and King, begin an investigation on the New York Museum of Classical Music being haunted by the angry, romantic soul of Mozart! Cliff had his first interrogation and Rigby went to a night of festivities over at the NYMCM.

This issue will see our crew deal with Mozart...or should I say, Mozart dealing with our crew? Looks like you have to read on to figure out!

Mirror, Mirror (Part 3)

The third and final chapter of the Mirror, Mirror sees Kelly get arrested, Vera get threatened, Kelly get violent and Stewart get busy with a lot of pretend girlfriends. To tell you more would just spoil it, so buy this comic right now and then brag about it to your friends. They'll be totally jealous of your great taste in comic books.
name: Mirror, Mirror (Part 3 of 3)

description:
Issue 3 The Prisoner

The Adventure Continues In issue 3.
name: The Prisoner

description: Beta and Hayden bring Roxy into the fold, while Oversight struggles to locate the reclusive Whitestone AI.
name: Chapter Six

description:
Come Together

After waking up from a 2-year coma, the young heroine Telepath struggled to find her place in the changed world. Now she and her best friend Motherboard are putting together a team of teen supers to try and accomplish together what they couldn't do on their own - but this group of misfits and loners may prove impossible to manage. Even as they struggle to find a way to work together, a monstrous new threat is released on an unsuspecting world.
name: Come Together

description: With tensions still rising, and the threat of oceanic war eminent. A peace meeting is called between the two main races, but not all involved want peace.
What is time? How much do we have and when is it over? And when it is over will we know and what would we expect?
Using powers bestowed upon him by mystical Feline Spirits. C.L.A.W.S. battles evildoers, and protects the citizens of New York City.

A new breed of superhero is born as legendary pro wrestler Chavo Guerrero stars in his first comic book adventure! When Chavo retires from the ring he uncovers a dark family secret and superhuman powers he never knew he had. He's going back for one more fight, but this time the stakes are amped!

Available in both English and Spanish Language Editions! Legendary pro wrestler Chavo Guerrero stars in his first comic book adventure! When Chavo retires from the ring he uncovers a dark family secret and superhuman powers he never knew he had. He's going back for one more fight, but this time the stakes are amped!

volume.name: El Credo del Guerrero de Chavo Guerrero

description:
Opening number

Meet the Pineapple Chunks, a punk rock band travelling across country for fame, fortune and that elusive record contract.

P.S: really not for kids!
name: Opening Number

description:
Courage. Tenacity. Spirit.

Danger Wolf is a story about a hero in the twilight of his career. Set in the early 80âs in the desert city of San Lazaro, our story takes place in a once thriving gambling mecca suffering from crime and urban rot after gambling was outlawed nearly overnight.
name: Part 1

description:
"DARKEST NIGHT: LOVE" is the first volume in the critically acclaimed Australian graphic novel series, following the trials and tribulations of 3 lives as they cross paths in Love, Death and Revenge.

BOOK ONE: After a tragic accident, Caleb must come to terms with the effects of guilt and grief, while stepping forward into adulthood, alone. Meanwhile, Carlie and Grant's new relationship blooms as Caleb attempts to see solace in the past, with dire consequences.
name: Volume One: Love

description: Boris Drude has one ambition in life, to get loaded and have a good time! He can ignore the ghost living in his closet and the fact that his new girlfriend won't kiss him, but when Reptilian Aliens take notice of him his life goes seriously off the rails! Omaha Perez (Holmes; Super Terre.r) takes a sly look at paranoia gone wild! Mind-bending cover by Tony Talbert (Xeric Award for First Moon) and Paul Mounts!
name: GN

volume.name: The Drude: Hanging Out and Hung Up On the Line

description:
Hap Hazard

1947: Berlin to Bikini Atoll to Roswell.

Timid teen Victoria (Vicky) Bond survives middle school by keeping her head down and trying not to get noticed. Her quiet life changes forever when she is bound to an exuberant super heroine. They must learn to work together in time to save their small town from a twisted robot with unique motivations of its own.

"My mind rebels at stagnation. Give me problems, give me work, give me the most abstruse cryptogram or the most intricate analysis, and I am in my own proper atmosphere." - Sherlock Holmes

As an Investigator, working in a special unit of the United Nations, Kathryn Monroe hunts the human predators who stalk this world.

Kathryn is resourceful, intelligent and has a deductive mind that is second to none. She is also bored...very,very bored.

Condemned to a desk job, while she 'learns the ropes', Kathryn longs for her first big case that will save her sanity.

Kathryn gets her wish when a child is abducted but her obsession with the case threatens to destroy her and everything she holds dear.

As she unravels the mystery Kathryn Monroe will learn that nothing about this case is as it seems.

Origins

The Adventures of Hero Ted, the Superhero Teddy Bear battling for truth, justice and a better bedtime. This Cuddly Hero is leading the way to defeat the Evil Boogeyman and his Legions of Monsters under the bed in his all-ages 28 page action comic book; written and drawn by Nick Davis.

Who Is Hero Ted?

Hero Ted is the Superhero alias of Teddy, a mild-mannered everyday Teddy Bear who snuggles up to his boy at night and accompanies him on his travels. But, when danger rears its head he puts on his child's security blanket, and in a flash of golden light turns into Hero Ted, the super-strong, flying Superhero for a younger generation.

His Comic Book -

The Adventures of Hero Ted are publishing in comic book form and feature two stories.

Origins - Gasp at the awesome Origin of Hero Ted as he discovers his powers the night the Monsters under the bed try to kidnap blankey

Terror In The Sand Pit - The Sand Pit comes to life and turns into a raging Monster! Can Hero Ted stop the Sand Pit Monsters rampage? before his child notices and never wants to go outside again?
name: Origins; Terror In The Sand Pit

description: Having someone you can count on is important, which is why Donny and Tyler are lucky, they've been best friends forever! They know each other better than they know themselves â sure, they can get on each other's nerves but so do all good friends. Life is pretty simple as the duo goes about their daily life in the ever-bustling city of London, looking for love, happiness and prosperity. Also they're Hitmen.

Victoria's visit with her scientist uncle Rudy in the Amazon rain-forest starts out with excitement and it keeps on going. It is a roller coaster from cover to cover... Rudy has disappeared and Victoria and her friends Scott must figure out what happened to him. They meet some shady characters along the way and plenty of scary snakes. You will end up smack dab in the middle of a mystery that is full of twists and turns.. but will Victoria and the gang figure it out? Whether you like snakes or hate em, you will LOVE "I HATE SNAKES".

Explored from the perspective of the courtesans of London, Jack the Hunted is a modern day retelling of the Jack the Ripper murders set in an alternative universe where the victims band together and fight back.

Mary Kelly, an exÂ­ call girl, returns to London to visit her old work friend, Polly, only to discover that she has been murdered in cold blood by a masked figure. Distraught by her friends death, Mary decides to join the Sorores Noctis, a clandestine society of courtesans who live and work together in order to keep one another safe from harm and corruption.
name: Chapter 1

description: Crispus hides who he is. Keeping his monstrous face beneath a mask, he avoids discovery by the oppressive, militaristic people of Hypocrium. But when his mask cracks, will that be the only thing to break?

MUTINY ON THE MOUSEY features the popular "Stinckers" mascots, Tiny Joe and Junior, as Captain Joe and his Master's Mate. Junior's diary entries detail the cruelty, romance and dangers faced on a long sea voyage with the merciless Captain Joe. The brilliant red skies and placid blue waters will excite your senses, while the modest price and digital format flatter your better judgement.

For the staff of Narbonics Labs, tampering in God's domain is just another day at the office. Mad scientist Helen Narbon is ready to show all those fools, ably assisted by geeky lab technician Dave, rifle-toting intern Mell, and Artie the superintelligent gerbil.

But Helen has secrets she keeps from the rest of the lab, and one of her experiments is about to wreak havoc beyond her wildest dreams...
name: Book One

description:
In the first book of this female lead Sci-Fi revenge series, Colonel Sienna McKnight obsessively pursues her mother's Killer. Experiments performed on an alien artifact give her & others around the globe exceptional abilities.

She fights for the fate of the WORLD and a unique orphan girl.

Kaya's Journey Begins Omnibus

In preparation for the release of Book 4, we're offering a Comixology Special - get the first 3 volumes (150 pages) of the Tailwands series for half the price of retail.

With the help of her family and friends, Kaya begins her journey into an amazing world of magic and mischief in the woodland realm of Silmay,
name: Vol. 1-3

description:
A Spectromancer Christmas Carol!

with the world teetering on the brink of Armageddon, it's important to remember the true meaning of Christmas! Don't miss Charles Dickens' classic tale, as narrated by special guest star Dandy Q. Dog! The world's fate may very well depend on it!
name: A Spectromancer Christmas Carol!

description:
Track 2

The story of Melodia continues as we meet Efex Petal and discover the part she and her Clef have to play in bringing the whole world to war...
name: Track 2

description: Our 12th compilation for Comixology of Aces Weekly â the award-winning on-screen comic art magazine featuring some of the world's finest creators of comic art. Published by David Lloyd, the guy who brought you V For Vendetta.
name: Vol. 12

description: So what exactly happened in Chile? Find out in this issue! Plus a Dollar Barn backup!
Kydra's rant has officially gone viral, and she's not happy about the effect it's having on her life. Bee, on the other, thinks she should be taking advantage of her spotlight.

Bleak Future

Sigma has bitten off more than she can chew. Her vendetta against President Valdes is out of her control. And her secret weapon, Ares, will not align his plans with hers. A local hacker is beginning to catch wind of the chaos brewing. Can anything be done?
name: Bleak Future

description:
Death Match

Dr. Wagner must fight for his life in order to win the Chem he needs to save his daughter's life.
name: Death Match

description:
Second Set

The CHUNKS have made it to L.A, but their first gig in the City of Angels is not exactly what they had in mind!
name: Second Set

description: Sister Long celebrates one year of being a full-time missionary, and things are starting to look up after the frigid and slow winter. She and her new companion encounter new obstacles but strive to teach with simplicity and love.
name: Month 13: February

volume.name: DENDO: One Year and One Half in Tokyo

description: In this number 2 of Doiditos, Maddog shows his talent like magician bewitching the enthusiastic Madmouse while it irritates the evil humoured Madcat.
name: Vol. 2: Doiditos Magic

description:
Battle 10

Making a deal with the Morris family, the ref manages to get Raid, June and Tempest into a match with Dae, Angel and Haze, fighting side by side against a squad of specially trained battlers to the death. With microphones broadcasting their strategies and a lack of co-ordination, Dae has no idea how to lead his team to victory.
name: Battle 10

description:
NEW STORIES! NEW CREATORS!

New comics by Dave Jordan (Where Do We Go From Here, Sadman), John Karnes (Jerks In Space), Westhoff & Ornelas (Bulletproof Chicken), Andy Tom (Low Concept), and stunning covers by John Bishop!

Through life, death, zombification, time travel, trips to the moon, and run-ins with the international Dave Conspiracy, Narbonics Labs has honed itself into a semi-formidable force of destruction. But as her staff disintegrates around her (not literally, this time), Helen Narbon finds herself up against the one evil genius who just might be a match for her.

Can love survive madness? Can the power of Science overcome common sense?
name: Book Two

description:
In a recognizable near future, Colonel Sienna McKnight obsessively pursues her mother's killer.

Lost and tortured, Sienna escapes into the shrouded night of Khorasan wielding a power she barely understands. Will Sienna be consumed by the darkness within?

Elsewhere, In Geneva, the world's largest machine probes its newest mystery: the Ansible. Who else will be affected when the hand of man touches the Promethean sphere of the heavens?

You're an agent for Project Skin Horse, the Black Ops Social Services agency that deals with the needs of America's nonhuman citizenry. It's another day at the office. Do you choose to investigate a terrorist attack on a transgenic rights meeting? Rescue a pair of teenagers who have come unstuck in time? Finally get licensed as a notary public? Or just boink the most attractive humanoid in the general vicinity?

No matter what you choose, turn to page 1. Because this volume contains these and many more incredibly daring experiences!
name: Volume Four

description:
When It Almost Happened Part Two

Garrison Hadge's secret comes to full light and the Earl is left scrambling trying to save his own skin.While hiding out in the manor, Raulph gains more information about the coming attempt on Christian's life, but did he hear right? Is Cromwell somehow involved? Meanwhile, Ravenwood and Pandora try to come to terms with the new change in their adventuring lives, while a group of guards make a surprise visit on the escapee Trolls and the Rats following them.
name: When It Almost Happened Part Two

description: Munro and his crew of misfit ex-cons are on their way to score the Warship that will give them a fighting chance against the Confederate forces on their heels, but getting their hands on the vessel won't be easy. With the entire fleet gathered for a grand galactic ceremony, they hope to sneak in as contract security and sneak out with their prize. But of course, the best plans always go south...

Finders Keepers

After striking a bargain with his intimidating new landlady, Rowen sets off to insure his stay by securing an income. He learns the value of money and hard work quickly in his new life among the villagers, but he doesn't forget the real reason he is there: to hunt down the goblins.

When all seems lost, he finally finds himself face to face with the goblin Greed. Will Rowen be ready to confront the thieving villain?
name: Finders Keepers

description: A man searches for meaning after the most destructive global attack in human history that took the lives of his wife & daughter. He travels throughout Europe and finds himself being suddenly guided to Africa. He discovers a great being of ancient knowledge known as Gaya who teaches him how to connect to all of consciousness and all of reality, to become the next savior of Earth - Atlas.

Welcome to the world of Baggywrinkles-a rollicking, educational survey of maritime lore, built around cartoonist Lucy Bellwood's time aboard tall ships. From the scourge of scurvy to the exhilaration of climbing the rigging for the first time, Lucy's comics bring the reader into a world of high seas history and informative adventure with "a sheer and unremitting sense of joy" [Andy Oliver, Broken Frontier].

Note: The digital edition (6/8/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

volume.name: Baggywrinkles: A Lubber's Guide To Life At Sea

description:
What makes someone kill? The age old question of nature (genetics) versus nurture (conditioning) is still open to debate. What is not open for debate is Brandonâs need to kill. But it isnât for revenge or fame or money...itâs for penance. He may have had the perfect life of being a model by day and partier by night but underneath he is a tormented, murderous soul. And as the investigating detectives along with the FBI find out, this is a motive enough that fuels a mad quest which can be unstoppable. Brandonâs coming for you, sinners. Collects issues 1 and 2. From writer Matt Nicholls (Collateral) and artist Simon Wright (Zombie Cities).

Note: The digital edition (6/8/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: GN

description:
All evil queens were princesses once.

A fading queen seeks to attain eternal beauty, no matter what it may cost her.

A Scar Is Born

The Roaring Twenties ...

A decade of wealth, excess and prosperity for many - but not all. While the successful segments of American society were living lavishly, the darker corners were spawning, shaping and honing the talents of young and enterprising criminals. With the impending doom of economic disaster looming, and the prohibition of narcotics and alcohol, the country, culture, and economics were primed for a new era of gangsterism to evolve.

Among the ensemble cast of soon-to-be crime kingpins ... arose one of the most prolific, mythologized, misunderstood, vilified and at times - idolized. His name was Salvatore Lucania, and in 1929, a near-death experience altered his physical appearance, produced outrageous misinformation, but most of all - cemented his status as the most infamous, influential, and polarizing organized crime figure in the annals of America's darker history.

Our story begins as ... a Scar is Born.

Martin "Mags" Reilly should have been the typical All-American teenager with boyish good looks, athletic prowess and a witty personality. But an incredible decision by his mother to inject him with a life-saving alien serum would forever intertwine their lives with the secret government organization called S.P.A.C.E. aka the Secret Planetary Agency for Containing Extraterrestrials.

Bearing the mark of an alien spore on his chest and alien cells streaming through his blood, Mags' is selected for a mission to the dark side of the moon to stop a burgeoning alien lifeform. Mags is protected, but the creature proves detrimental to a fellow astronaut, who turns against Mags, his S.P.A.C.E. colleagues--and Mags' own mother!

Now that the stakes are higher than ever before, Mags Reilly must follow the path he started down as a young boy by finally embracing his destiny. And with the help of a special S.P.A.C.E.-designed suit tuned to his alien biology, he becomes Moonshot, the space age superhero! But in a universe where most of the caped heroes were all killed years earlier and his own abilities still developing in ways he can't quite control (like zipping through the space-time continuum!), Moonshot must learn to play the superhero game and take his place along with Green Owl, Harrowing, and others in the all-new Owlverse!
name: Mystery In S.P.A.C.E.

description:
To save his city, a hero must rebel against a totalitarian regime led by his deadly alter ego.

Andrew Fuller swore to use his supernatural powers to protect Washington DC. His second personality, Riven, swore to protect Andrew. But when the two personas are permanently split, Riven mysteriously awakens nine years in the future to a ruthless police state governed by Andrew Fuller and his oppressive military defense androids. Racing to uncover the truth of their separation, Riven is forced to make a decision: to free his city, he must kill the one man he is sworn to protect.

A woman escapes heartbreak into the cold of Earth's orbit where she collects and monitors and collects floating debris. However, her distant memories of Earth beckon her to re-enter the atmosphere to confront her losses. Comes with a copy of RGBmono's upcoming album and bonus songs.

Trans.versal

Trans.versal is the Silencing's opening act, introducing you to its near-future, sci-fi, dystopian world, beasts, and two of the many forthcoming characters.
name: Chapter 1: Trans.Versal

description:
STAR MISSIONS is a new Science Fiction Adventure series that takes place in the early 23rd century. Man has successfully populated distant star systems and for the past 25 years lived peacefully among the two alien worlds in the "Strolla System".

All of that is about to change and the series begins.

Follow the adventures of Blue-ray, Amanda, Governor Belter, Colonel Hand and a great cast of characters, Terran and Alien alike as they strive to survive beyond the "Angel's Gate" in the Strolla System and beyond.
name: Intro & The Swarm

description:
The orienteers

Zak & Ting are not really doing anything in the city of Gothenburg, Sweden. When Ting finds a orienteering map it catches her interest...
name: The Orienteers

description:
It's Time for Spectromaniacs!

The Worner Brothers have served Spectro, and now he has to make a serious change in his brand! Also: Cull returns to face off with Spectro and this time he brings some friends!
name: It's Time For Spectromaniacs!

description:
Track 3

The final issue in Volume 1 closes with an epic finale. All of our cast meet a hooded figure with mysterious motives...
name: Track 3

description:
Through Science, A Requiem

Chapter 4 of this 6-part series: In the depths of space, the scientists investigate the newly discovered alien ship. A brilliant, but nefarious physician conducts an insidious experiment, and the mission's commanders prepare for the worst.

Note: The digital edition (6/15/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Chapter 4: Through Science, A Requiem

description:
Sisters in Arms

The first issue of Act 2 gives us a zombie bashing good time when Jamie meets up with Dream Realm Entertainment's "Faint: The Slasher Slayer!"
name: Sisters in Arms

description:
Trapped

Dr. Wagner is held prisoner by the cartel.
name: Trapped

description: The trios of Muse, Mercury and The Badger have one last stop before returning home: The swinging 60's! They literally drop in on a young Judo Girl battling cat burglar Hepcat. She's been tracking the crafty thief across the globe, as he's been stealing parts for Captain Steel. The Muse decides to help Judo Girl as she breaks into Captain's Steel secret lair, James Bond style! There they discover that Steel has been assembling a powerful device. One that can free him from time and space itself. And it means a possible way home for Muse, Mercury and The Badger! This is the thrilling conclusion to the Crossed Wires mini series. Will Badger ever return home to his dimension? And what happens when Muse and Mercury finish their dark showdown? Guest starring Judo Girl!

A Tale of Two Demons

Greydon marches his army towards the Slave Pens, looking to defeat the Demons and liberate the Humans and Cyclops that are trapped within. His army exhausted and in desperate need of shelter, Greydon seeks refuge in the Burning Forest, the home to the all powerful fire demon, Ifrit.

Within the Slave Pens, Emily tries to sow the seeds of rebellion, hoping to cause the demons to fight a war on two fronts. It is a difficult task but as we discover, there is much more to Emily than meets the eye.
name: A Tale of Two Demons

description:
The Emotional Lives of Engineers - Part 3

Can machines have souls? This is a central question being mulled about in Shae's artificial mind as she tries to find answers from the galaxy's leading spiritual authority. The surprising answer would help her confront Albertron, whose sophomoric antics eventually led to Shae's origin. Join this pair as skeletons get dragged out of the closet and startling revelations determine their course forward. What will happen to their friendship when the truth is laid out? And what is the nature of that friendship? Does their love extend beyond the platonic?
name: The Emotional Lives of Engineers Part 3

description:
Chapter 5: The Monster

Over the course of his career, super-scientist inventor George Baker has changed the world several times over with the help of his team at Noreon Labs. Edward Varius has been Baker's right-hand-man and second-in-command for all those years.

When their most recent invention, retinal implants known as "Cyber-Eyes," starts malfunctioning in bizarre and inexplicable ways, Baker is sent on a globe-trotting hunt for answers that lead him to a monstrous and explosive encounter aboard a supersonic train.

Meanwhile, Varius reflects on the past...
name: Chapter 5: The Monster

description: Kurt Cobain, Amy Winehouse, Adele, Bono. Geniuses all, Kurt Cobain and Amy Winehouse exemplify the epitome of talents taken from us too soon, while Bono's generation-spanning gift offers stability and relative newcomer Adele proffers hope. Icons of Rock #4 presents the life stories of musicians with talents that will be long-remembered.
name: Volume 4

description: The next leg of the journey on wide open grasslands leaves all our heroes out of their element. The local fauna aren't too keen on trespassers, but what will they think of a human who can talk to them? Even better question, will Joe and Sister stop bickering long enough to get to their destination?

volume.name: The Lost Island of the Na-Rune-Tok

description:
A Perfect Triangle

From the ruins of Old Santa Monica to the peaks of the Silver City's spires, it all comes down to this! In the epic climax to "Paradise High," Alex is trapped, and the only way out -- is a long way down.
name: Paradise High -The Finale- A Perfect Triangle

description:
Christmas 2015

It's Christmas time and Stella has 3 seasonal stories to tell! A great big Merry Christmas to New Stuff readers everywhere!
name: Christmas 2015

description:
The adventure continues as Nexus has been banished by the world-eater GOURMANDO to a foreboding mist filled dimension. Powerless, Nexus befriends an odd alien creature - the Larp! And as if things couldn't get any weirder, the BADGER makes an appearance! You don't want to miss this one!

The Nexus Newspaper strip is made in the tradition of the classic newspaper strips and at classic newspaper strip size of 17" x 22"! You have to see these in person to truly appreciate them!

Included here is Nexus Comic Strips #12-15 plus pages from "When She was Young", a fully painted story featuring Sundra Peale in her college days that was originally published in Nexus 100. Extra features include the strip "Out There" by Bill Waist and a look back on the Badger's first appearance in Nexus #6!

The award-nominated UK superhero soap opera series continues!

The O Men want to destroy the Vicious Circle II and the Vultures terrorist organisation â and they've got a plan. Will it work? Prepare for shocks, twists and violence in the first part of a special two-part story called... 'Danger of Death'.

Stranded!

Justice International agent Rob Hanes is hired to extradite a beautiful female convict back to the U.S. and becomes stranded with her on a desert island after their plane goes down in the Pacific.
name: Stranded!
